findings.heart: Normal in size and without pericardial effusion.

abdominal.biliary_system: No intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation.
abdominal.kidneys: Enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast normally without evidence of hydronephrosis or solid renal mass.
abdominal.appendix: Retrocecal, fluid-filled and dilated to 12 mm with associated mucosal hyperemia.
abdominal.fat_stranding: Significant adjacent fat stranding compatible with appendicitis.
abdominal.peritoneum: No evidence of frank pneumoperitoneum or organized fluid collection.
abdominal.bowel: Stomach, duodenum, and intra-abdominal loops of small and large bowel are normal in caliber without evidence of wall thickening or obstruction.
abdominal.lymph_nodes: No pathologically enlarged retroperitoneal lymph nodes seen.

findings.bones: No osseous destructive lesions concerning for malignancy detected.
